snippet: Initial claims for unemployment benefits declined last week, and economists said the downward trajectory raised chances that May would be the fifth consecutive month with job gains greater than 200,000.
abstract: Labor Department reports that applications for weekly unemployment benefits fell 26,000 to a seasonally adjusted 319,000; decline is more than expected, indicating that labor market is strengthening despite a run-up in initial applications in previous weeks.
lead_paragraph: Initial claims for unemployment benefits declined last week, and economists said the downward trajectory raised chances that May would be the fifth consecutive month with job gains greater than 200,000.

headline.main: Jobless Claims Fall More Than Expected
headline.print_headline: Jobless Claims Fall More Than Expected
